  SpeakerName: Monk Uthai
  DialogueText: In ancient times, sandalwood was a rare and precious material reserved
    for the elite. Its use in funerals originated from the belief that its scent
    would carry the soul of the departed to the afterlife in a dignified and peaceful
    manner.
